tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters, including glucose, HbA1c, renal function, electrolytes, and calcium, are within normal limits. There is no laboratory evidence of diabetes, renal dysfunction, or electrolyte imbalance at this time. No acute or chronic metabolic disturbances are apparent from these results.
